xxl.core.indexStructures

Class Entry.WithKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.indexStructures.Entry.WithKey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable
    Enclosing class:
    Entry

    public static class Entry.WithKey
extends Object
implements Comparable
    Querying data from a IndexedSet is done by queries over the keys. You can easily query for data with this class. Suppose relationalSet is an instance of BPlusIndexedSet. Independent of the Schema you can perform e.g. an existence check for an entry with the key {2,4} like the following example shows 
    
  Entry.WithKey element = new Entry.WithKey(2,4);
  boolean result = relationalSet.contains(element);
    Please note, that each component of a Entry.WithKey have to be Comparable and should match the tables Schema.
